# Phase I â€“ In-Memory Console Todo Application ## Context This specification defines Phase I of the "Evolution of Todo" project. The goal is to build a basic console-based Todo application using Spec-Driven Development. All code must be generated by AI. Human must not write code manually. --- ## Objective Create a Python console application that allows a user to manage a Todo list in memory. --- ## Technology Constraints - Language: Python 3.13 - Interface: Console / CLI - Storage: In-memory only - No external libraries - No file system usage - No network calls --- ## Data Model Todo: - id: integer (auto-increment, unique) - title: string - description: string - completed: boolean (default: false) Todos are stored in a list during runtime. --- ## Functional Requirements ### Add Todo - Prompt user for title and description - Create a new todo item - Assign unique ID - Set completed to false - Store in memory --- ### View Todos - Display all todos - Show: - ID - Title - Completion status (Completed / Pending) - If no todos exist, show a clear message --- ### Update Todo - Prompt user for todo ID - Allow updating: - title - description - If ID does not exist, display an error message --- ### Delete Todo - Prompt user for todo ID - Remove todo from memory - If ID does not exist, display an error message --- ### Mark Todo Complete / Incomplete - Prompt user for todo ID - Toggle completed status - If ID does not exist, display an error message --- ## User Interaction Flow - Display a numbered menu: 1. Add Todo 2. View Todos 3. Update Todo 4. Delete Todo 5. Mark Complete / Incomplete 6. Exit - Menu repeats until user selects Exit --- ## Error Handling - Invalid menu input must not crash the application - Invalid todo ID must show a user-friendly error --- ## Acceptance Criteria - Application runs without errors - All five core features function correctly - Data exists only during application runtime - Output is clear and readable in the console